Day 4 of #100DaysOfData 🎯
The most valuable skill in data isn't SQL, Python, or ML.
It's communication.

A stakeholder once asked me for an alerts report. 
Instead of immediately building it, I asked a few simple questions:
🎯 What problem are we trying to solve? 
👤 Who will use this? 
💡 What decision should this report help with?
That conversation changed everything.
The request sounded right — but the actual need was different. 

Once we understood the real goal, the right solution became clear.

One thing I've learned in data: 
Great analysts don't just work with numbers. 
They translate problems into clarity.

Technical skills help you build. 
Communication helps you create impact.

If this was useful, follow along.
